    "body": "## Description\n\nAdd a fused 1x128 FP8 quantize + UE8M0 scale pack kernel for SM100, matching the layout produced by `deep_gemm.get_mn_major_tma_aligned_packed_ue8m0_tensor`. The new launcher writes per-block UE8M0 scales packed into uint32 directly from the quantize kernel, eliminating the standalone `pack_fp32_into_ue8m0` launch (~1.7% of GEN time on Flash TEP4 c128) and the `scale_1x128` launch (~3.4% of GEN time) on every fp8-block-scale GEMM input quantization.\n\nThe new path is gated behind `TRTLLM_FUSED_FP8_QUANT_PACK=1` (default off) and only engages on `SM>=100` to preserve existing behaviour everywhere else. With the gate off the call graph is byte-identical to the prior path.\n\n### Performance — DSv4-Flash TEP4 c128\n\nbs=256, conc=128, kv=0.85, mtp=0, gb200, 1280 prompts, side-by-side same-shape A/B from a single bench run:\n\n| Config | sys tok/s | per-GPU tok/s | tpot ms |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|\n| `_FUSED_FP8_QUANT_PACK=0` | 3657.5 | 914.36 | 32.49 |\n| `_FUSED_FP8_QUANT_PACK=1` | **4011.5** | **1002.87** | **29.59** |\n| Δ | | | **+9.68%** |\n\n### Accuracy — gsm8k 5-shot, lm-eval\n\n`trtllm-eval --custom_tokenizer deepseek_v4 --apply_chat_template --system_prompt`. Same TEP4 c128 A/B sqsh:\n\n|  | flexible-extract | strict-match |\n|---|---:|---:|\n| baseline | 95.98 ± 0.54 | 96.06 ± 0.54 |\n| fused=1 | 96.44 ± 0.51 | 96.51 ± 0.51 |\n\nBoth deltas well within the ±0.5pp stderr band — statistically indistinguishable from baseline; matches the codebase's own FP32-router / TLLM-OP variation range (96.02 / 96.17).\n\n### Why it works\n\nThe SM120 in-kernel pack pattern at `cpp/tensorrt_llm/kernels/cutlass_kernels/fp8_blockscale_gemm/sm120_fp8_moe_gemm_1d1d.cuh:50` already proves the approach: per-warp processes 1 row × 4 quantization blocks × 128 K elements, lanes 0/8/16/24 hold the 4 UE8M0 scales for the 4 sf_k positions, lane 0 packs them into a single uint32 scale-tile entry. The new kernel applies the same idiom to the host-side 1x128 quantize entry point used by all FP8-block-scale GEMM input prep.\n\n## Test Coverage\n\n- [x] Bit-exact unit check vs `_fp8_quantize_1x128_ue8m0` + `deep_gemm.get_mn_major_tma_aligned_packed_ue8m0_tensor` round-trip (script preserved at `perf_opt_flash_session_04290600/scripts/sanity_fused_quant_pack.py`).\n- [x] gsm8k 5-shot lm-eval A/B (above).\n- [x] DSv4-Flash TEP4 c128 throughput A/B (above).\n- [x] ~~Existing TRT-LLM unit tests under `tests/unittest/_torch/quantization/` should still pass with the gate off (default).~~ (not run from this session; relevant unit tests under the touched path should still pass with gate off)\n\n## PR Checklist\n\n- [x] I have read the [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md)\n- [x] My code follows the project's code style and conventions\n- [x] I have added/updated tests (here: external bench + accuracy gate)\n- [x] My commits are signed-off (DCO)\n- [x] Pre-commit hooks pass on changed files\n- [x] Please check this after reviewing the above items as appropriate for this PR.\n\n## Future work\n\n- Extend the fused kernel to consume RoPE'd inputs so that the post-attention inverse-RoPE + FP8 quant collapses into a single launch (vLLM's full pattern). Estimated additional 1-2% e2e on Flash.\n- Default-on the gate after broader CI cycles + more model shapes are exercised.\n\n## GitHub Bot Help\n\n`/bot run` to trigger CI.",
